{
  "stem": "1677.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had to, all right, march out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I came home and I cried so bitterly.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's the first time and the only time I remember I cried.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I never cried.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I had no reason to cry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I cried, and I said to my father, You should have sent me to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I should have gone on child aliyah.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was a very, very lucrative thing for the Zionist movement.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You paid in Swiss francs or pounds sterling the full education of your child.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "A pittance.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It wasn't very much money for wealthy people like my parents.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And for that, the child aliyah== which I think still exists-- took upon themselves to educate you.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You're talking about me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember that shops, by '39 it was getting very tough.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Shops had to have an Aryan manager who kicked them out as soon as he could.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My parents had a very nice [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] help in the shop, Jankol Hantag.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He's still in an old age home in Puchov.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Still there.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I write to him every Christmas.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this Jankol Hantag, I think, from what I was told, was an illegitimate son of one of my uncles, and they gave him to my family to make him a nice businessman.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He drove the truck, he counted eggs, he fixed the butter, he was behind the counter, he was Jankol.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father, who was very intelligent, made a voluntary Aryanization.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they gave him-- gave him, virtually-- 40% of the business, and kept 60%.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Which allowed my father to still be in the business with my mother.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My grandfather died 1940, when he was 80 years of age, in his sleep, luckily.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
